properties.AltName: Kentuckuy Ohio West Virginia Interstate Planning Commission

properties.Description: The City of Elizabethtown is awarded $11.1 million in funding to improve safety in three key locations: Ring Road, Leitchfield Road, and US 31W.
The City of Danville is awarded $12.2 million in funding for the design and construction of pedestrian facilities, roundabouts, and restricted crossing U-turn intersections.
This award will be used by the City of Versailles to conduct four quick-build demonstration projects that will then inform their comprehensive safety action plan.
This award will be used by City of London to develop a comprehensive safety action plan.
This award will be used by Boone County Fiscal Court to install a High Frictions Surface Treatment (HFST) and improved shouldering at five locations, demonstrating its efficacy.

The Henderson County Fiscal Court is awarded $3.3 million in funding to build cost-effective safety measures to address crashes in a high-traffic, heavily rural-agricultural area of western Kentucky bordered to the north by the Ohio River and Evansville,
This award will be used by the Cumberland Valley ADD to create a safety action plan that focuses on proven safety countermeasures.

This award will be used by the FIVCO Area Development District to develop a Comprehensive Safety Action plan to address crash fatalities and injuries with a focus on single vehicle crashes in rural areas and vulnerable users in urbanized areas.
